3040	// Sequence: (1) ensconce busybox naturally -> mint touchmark S, read it back;
3041	// (2) ensconce busybox pinned to S -> identical digest, guard's idempotent
3042	// branch, exit 0; (3) ensconce debian pinned to S -> different digest under the
3043	// same touchmark, guard's collision branch, host exit non-zero; (4) banish S.
3044	//
3045	// The collision verdict rests on the HOST EXIT CODE: the guard's "touchmark
3046	// collision" message lands in Cloud Logging (CLOUD_LOGGING_ONLY), not host
3047	// stdout, but a cloud build FAILURE propagates to a non-zero rbw-lE exit
3048	// (rbfcb_BuildHost.sh: status != SUCCESS -> buc_die). The idempotent step (2) is
3049	// the positive control: the identical pipeline on the same pinned touchmark
